    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-12-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10170.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 139.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to the Mexican Embassy’s note of
                    March 10, 1906,<note n="1" xml:id="d567fn1">Not printed.</note> and to
                    subsequent correspondence regarding the extradition of George Deering Reed to
                    Mexico, I have the honor to inform you <pb facs="0700" n="598" xml:id="pg_598"/>
                    that the department is in receipt of a telegram, dated the 2d instant, from the
                    Attorney General, in which he says: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Referring to your letter March 13, 1906, and subsequent correspondence, I
                            have the honor to report that George Deering Reed is under arrest and
                            provisional detention in the district of New Jersey, charged with
                            embezzlement in Mexico.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
